reviews.review_text: Excellent Quality Audience Tape from Peak Era As a lover of '78 shows, I was searching for something really hot with a bit of audience applause and cheering in the background.   This show cooks for many reasons, but I particularly love its diversity.  From TLEO to Samson & Delilah to the Mississippi Half Step opener, the show just seems to have it all.  Rocks, gets trippy, brings you back, ballads, westerns, etc.   Just epic.   Donna sounds great, which wasn't always the case, and is mixed in appropriately.   Liked it so much, I had to go back and listen to the first set twice in a row.  Will play this one over and over again -- it's a new favorite!
Mellow~ This is a great AUD pull of a strong and somewhat mellow show.  I enjoyed this one start to finish!!
